Image 9 of 9 Harris knocked out as Steele rolls past Clemens 1 / 9 Back to Gallery The crowd that waited to find their seats at Lehnhoff Stadium sat in silence for a few moments Friday night.
Clemens quarterback Frank Harris evaded Steeleâ€™s pass rush yet again and was on the verge of another big run until Knights senior defensive end Mark Jackson quickly tackled him into the ground.
The crowd exhaled when Harris got up, kept his left arm still and walked straight to the locker room. The junior watched the rest of the game from the sideline as Steele picked up a 31-7 district victory.
